<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="109" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
This species grows above 3000 to 4300 m in grassy alpine meadows. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schltr., Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 20: 381" authorityYear="1924" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Habenaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Habenaria balfouriana" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balfouriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Habenaria balfouriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted distribution in the southern Hengduan Mountains, sharing the habitat with the similar-looking 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. aitchisonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="aitchisonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">H. aitchisonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Though 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. aitchisonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="aitchisonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">H. aitchisonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. balfouriana" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="balfouriana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">H. balfouriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found closely allied in a recent molecular study (
<bibRefCitation DOI="http://dx.doi.org/10.1186/s12870-017-1160-x" author="Jin, WT" journalOrPublisher="Reeve &amp; Co., London" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B12" refString="Jin, WT, Schuiteman, A, Chase, MW, Li, JW, Chung, SW, Hsu, TC, Jin, XH, 2017. Phylogenetics of subtribe Orchidinae s.l. (Orchidaceae; Orchidoideae) based on seven markers (plastid matK, psaB, rbcL, trnL-F, trnH-psba, and nuclear nrITS, Xdh): implications for generic delimitation. BMC Plant Biology 17(1-14): e222. http://dx.doi.org/10.1186/s12870-017-1160-x" title="Phylogenetics of subtribe Orchidinae s. l. (Orchidaceae; Orchidoideae) based on seven markers (plastid matK, psaB, rbcL, trnL-F, trnH-psba, and nuclear nrITS, Xdh): implications for generic delimitation. BMC Plant Biology 17 (1 - 14): e 222." url="http://dx.doi.org/10.1186/s12870-017-1160-x" year="2017">Jin et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
), they are distinct morphologically; both have yellowish-green flowers with bilobed petals, but the former has an elongated spur that exceeds the length of the ovary and pedicel (versus spur shorter than ovary in 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. aitchisonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="aitchisonii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">H. aitchisonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
